<div class="entry-content primary-content-column columns small-12 medium-8">
<p><span class="wf_caption" style="display: block; max-width: 640px; width: 100%;"><noscript><img src="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/legacy/images/images_2017_08/2017_0807ubi.jpg" alt="Author Jurgen De Wispelaere speaks at the Bien Congress 2014 in Montreal, Canada, June 28, 2014. (Photo: BICN / RCRG Basic Income Canada Network; Edited: LW / TO)" width="640" style="width: 100%; margin: auto;"></noscript><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203%202'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Author Jurgen De Wispelaere speaks at the Bien Congress 2014 in Montreal, Canada, June 28, 2014. (Photo: BICN / RCRG Basic Income Canada Network; Edited: LW / TO)" width="640" style="width: 100%; margin: auto;" data-src="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/legacy/images/images_2017_08/2017_0807ubi.jpg" loading="lazy"><span style="text-align: left; margin-top: 3px; display: block;">Author Jurgen De Wispelaere speaks at the Bien Congress 2014 in Montreal, Canada, June 28, 2014. (Photo: <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/125136781@N03/14388264580/in/photolist-nVmVVu-ocRNfa-nVrBMf-ocJgxb-ocKGb5-oaU97d-ocWtUT">BICN / RCRG Basic Income Canada Network</a>; Edited: LW / TO)</span></span></p>
<p>As one of the world&rsquo;s leading scientific experts on universal basic income (UBI), Jurgen De Wispelaere has <a href="https://bath.academia.edu/JurgenDeWispelaere">written</a> books and numerous articles on UBI, in addition to having edited several volumes on the topic. He is currently a political economy research fellow at the Independent Social Research Foundation and a policy research fellow at the Institute for Policy Research, University of Bath. He was previously a visiting research fellow at the University of Tampere, where he was a consultant on the research team preparing Finland&rsquo;s current national basic income <a href="https://www.kela.fi/web/en/experimental-study-on-a-universal-basic-income">experiment</a>.</p>
<p>In this interview, De Wispelaere outlines the most important aspects of UBI &mdash; its feasibility, what we can learn from previous experiments, why the right implementation is so important and how UBI touches our basic philosophy of human nature. De Wispelaere&rsquo;s core argument is that the best reason for pursuing the UBI agenda is ending poverty.</p><div class="truth-post-content-high  inline-callout-container" id="truth-255792"><aside class=" callout inline-callout callout--subscribe callout--dark" id="truth-255397">
<h2>The stories you care about, right at your fingertips</h2>
<p>Get <em>Truthout&rsquo;</em>s daily edition delivered to your inbox.</p>
